mproving client experience + Participate in client visits and service review/scorecard meetings + Project work (Regulatory, Strategic/Platform, Exchange/Product onboarding, AI/Blockchain implementations) Skills and Qualifications + General Cleared Derivatives -- F&O/Cleared Swaps (OTC) -- industry knowledge (5+ years experience required) + Detailed F&O/OTC exchange / product knowledge for global markets across all asset classes + Proven skills in delivering a professional face to our clients and taking ownership of issues through to closure + Experience in handling a client base consisting of Banks, Hedge Funds, Pension Funds, Insurance Companies, Asset Managers, Commodity Trading Advisors, Corporates, Utility Companies, Oil Companies & Food Companies + Holistic understanding of operations & front office responsibilities in servicing cleared derivatives clients + Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to communicate across multiple functional units and seniority levels + Ability to identify process improvements that drive capacity, efficiency and controls + Strong communication and messaging skills + Stakeholder mentality + Ability to work accurately and effectively under pressure + Strong time management skills required to meet critical deadlines and prioritize + Practical Industry & business application skills required (GMI, Microsoft Excel, Visio, Sharepoint). Advanced capabilities (GMI query, VBA, SQL) highly preferred + Experience in designing solutions using analytics, reporting, and automation tools preferred (Alteryx, Xceptor, Tableau, Qlikview) Would suit someone looking for a flexible working opportunity JPMorgan Chase & Co . offers an exceptional benefits program and a highly competitive compensation package. JPMorgan Chase is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer Disability/Veteran.JPMorgan Chase & Co., one of the oldest financial institutions, offers innovative financial solutions to millions of consumers, small businesses and many of